  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Manager (Maritime ERP)",
  "description": "<h3>Role Overview</h3><p>The Sales Manager will drive new business for a <strong>Maritime Accounting ERP platform</strong>, selling to shipowners, operators, and ship management companies. The role requires strong <strong>maritime industry knowledge</strong> and a <strong>systems/technical background</strong>, with the ability to translate accounting, financial, and operational requirements into effective digital solutions.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Own the full sales cycle from lead generation to deal closure</p></li><li><p>Develop new business within shipowners, operators, and ship managers</p></li><li><p>Conduct client discovery sessions focused on <strong>accounting, finance, and reporting workflows</strong></p></li><li><p>Position ERP solutions covering:</p><ul><li><p>Vessel & management accounting</p></li><li><p>AP/AR, billing, and financial reporting</p></li><li><p>Budgeting, cost control, and voyage / fleet profitability</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Deliver solution demos and support proof-of-concepts</p></li><li><p>Build relationships with Finance Managers, CFOs, Technical and Operations teams</p></li><li><p>Work closely with pre-sales, product, and implementation teams</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>5+ years of experience in <strong>maritime sales or solutions consulting</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong exposure to <strong>maritime accounting systems, ERP, or finance platforms</strong></p></li><li><p>Background in <strong>Systems Engineering, IT, Marine Engineering, or Accounting-related systems</strong></p></li><li><p>Solid understanding of <strong>shipping accounting and cost structures</strong></p></li><li><p>Proven consultative / solution-selling experience</p></li></ul>",
